Not Just Facebook and LinkedIn. Networks in Healthcare Operations.¶

Management at a glance.¶

Motivation¶

  • Healthcare is complex.
  • Multiple stakeholders, and Interests.(clinical, financial, operational)
  • information overload. No shortage of information, but wanting insight.

Why networks¶

  • Modelling relationship.
  • Lends itself to modelling complex systems.
  • Makes for intuitive visualizations

Examples to be discussed today.¶

  • Referral networks of patients, and the question of access to care.
  • Simulation of operation.
  • Future applications, patterns of practice and benchmarking, fraud revenue generators,

Lets get started with the basics¶

Recap.¶

What else do we need.¶

We know:¶

  • rate of referrals
  • time it take to service the referral.
  • structure of the network i.e. "who refers to who"

We are interested in:¶

  • count of patients in the queue
  • count of clinics that are in overflow.

How might this look for a whole healthcare system.¶
